==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glossic
<hw>Glos"sic</hw> <pr>(gl⟦ocr⟧s"s⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>glossa</ets> a word requiring a gloss. See 3d
<er>Gloss</er>.]</ety> <def>A system of phonetic spelling based upon the
present values of English letters, but invariably using one symbol to
represent one sound only.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ingglish <qex>Glosik</qex> konvai⟦middot⟧z hwotev⟦middot⟧er
proanusiai⟦middot⟧shon iz inten⟦middot⟧ded bei dhi reiter.</q>
<rj><qau>A. J. Ellis.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glossily</ent>⟦br⟧
